<subSubSection id="3B4AA1F8F3BA456AC02E4F8F888BA23C" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F2CE5B35FEC4133F0283FD3DEB51F323" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FFF220D82CBE0133069F2F81D12B0696" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
The species epithet, 
<taxonomicName id="D486A546EF4807B718E6A3DDA1764FD2" authority="Konstantinov &amp; Linzmeier, 2020" authorityName="Konstantinov &amp; Linzmeier" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Erinaceialtica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="rileyi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rileyi">rileyi</taxonomicName>
, is a patronym in honor of Ed Riley, who contributed greatly to our knowledge of diversity and taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName id="E750731408FBC1C2849F2119F78B9F02" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" family="Chrysomelidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="family">Chrysomelidae</taxonomicName>
in the United States and the New World in general.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
